OL,3,CFood crops wilt in the heat as
OL,4,Csupermarket bills rise
OL,6,FOn Thriplow Farms in Hertfordshire,
OL,7,Fthe harvest has started early.
OL,9,FFarmer David Walston says his hand has
OL,10,Fbeen forced by the extreme weather.
OL,12,FThe wheat, oats, and barley grown here
OL,13,Fgo into bread, breakfast cereals,
OL,14,Fbeer, and animal feed - staples of the
OL,15,FBritish diet.
OL,17,FBut with little rain and intense heat,
OL,18,Fthe crops have withered.
