OL,3,CFood crops wilt in the heat as
OL,4,Csupermarket bills rise
OL,6,F"I suspect I will remember this year
OL,7,Fas the worst harvest for decades - and
OL,8,Fhopefully the worst of my career,"
OL,9,Fsays Walston.
OL,11,FYields are down, here and across much
OL,12,Fof Europe. At the same time, food
OL,13,Fprices are edging up.
OL,15,FThe headline rate of inflation rose
OL,16,Funexpectedly to 3.6% last month,
OL,17,Fdriven by food, fuel, airfares and
OL,18,Frail tickets.
