OL,4,Csupermarket bills rise
OL,6,FIn June, UK inflation was higher than
OL,7,Fin Italy, Germany, France or the
OL,8,FUnited States - and well above the
OL,9,FBank of England's 2% target.
OL,11,FPrice growth has picked up modestly in
OL,12,Frecent months, but economists do not
OL,13,Fexpect anything like the surge of
OL,14,F2022, when inflation peaked above 11%.
OL,16,FRoughly half the food we eat is
OL,17,Fproduced in the UK, with most of the
OL,18,Frest imported from the EU - which is
OL,19,Falso suffering from extreme weather.
